VR180 Conversion
Overview

VR180 Conversion is a web application designed to convert 3D 360° videos into immersive VR180 format. This tool is particularly useful for content creators and developers working with VR180 videos, enabling them to convert and view their content in a VR headset for a more immersive experience.

Live Demo

Explore the live application here: https://vr180-conversion.onrender.com/

Features

3D 360° to VR180 Conversion: Transform 360° videos into VR180 format for immersive viewing.

Real-Time Preview: View the converted content directly in your browser before finalizing.

User-Friendly Interface: Simple and intuitive design for ease of use.

Technologies Used

Frontend: React, Tailwind CSS

Backend: Express.js

Video Processing: FFmpeg

Database: PostgreSQL

Authentication: Passport.js

State Management: React Query

Setup Instructions

To run this project locally, follow these steps:

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/kushal1929/VR180_conversion.git
cd VR180_conversion


Install dependencies:

npm install


Set up environment variables:

Create a .env file in the root directory and add the following:

DATABASE_URL=your_database_url
SESSION_SECRET=your_session_secret


Run the development server:

npm run dev


The application will be available at http://localhost:3000
.

Deployment

This application is deployed on Render. For deployment on other platforms, ensure the following:

Node.js: Version 18.x

Build Command: npm run build

Start Command: npm run start

